  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pseudobulbar Affect is a condition characterized by frequent episodes of laughing and crying
      out of proportion. Other terms used to describe this condition include emotional lability,
      emotionalism, emotion incontinence, emotional discontrol, excessive emotionalism and
      pathological laughing and crying. AVP-923 is a new experimental drug that may assist in the
      reduction of uncontrolled episodes. This study will test the safety and efficacy of AVP-923
      in the treatment of MS patients suffering from pseudobulbar affect.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
